      "text": "A 32-year-old zoologist returns from a 6-month assignment studying tapirs in the Brazilian rainforest and presents with a 5-day history of illness. Initial symptoms included sudden high fever, severe headache, and vomiting, which completely resolved after 3 days. The patient now presents with recurrent fever, epistaxis, coffee-ground emesis, and severe abdominal pain. Laboratory studies show thrombocytopenia, elevated transaminases, and prolonged PTT. What is the most likely current period of this patient's disease?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Intoxication period"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Secondary bacterial infection"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Critical period"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Recurrent infection period"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Recrudescence period"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- This patient presents with the classic three-period progression of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=U50bjg&anker=Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"U50bjg\" data-anker=\"Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-sememe-id=\"8L0Ozg\">yellow fever</a>: an initial infection period with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=YL0nwg&anker=Z67ba0252fff6842349617790ed19ae54\" data-learningcard-id=\"YL0nwg\" data-anker=\"Z67ba0252fff6842349617790ed19ae54\" data-sememe-id=\"tK0XRS\">headache</a>, followed by a remission period with symptom resolution, and finally, an intoxication period, which occurs in approximately 15% of symptomatic patients. Hemorrhagic manifestations including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hj0KbT&anker=Z5c2e48c03f4f7ffb7eba5810a71d5839\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hj0KbT\" data-anker=\"Z5c2e48c03f4f7ffb7eba5810a71d5839\" data-sememe-id=\"Vm0Geg\">epistaxis</a> and coffee-ground emesis, combined with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wT0hG2&anker=Zdab14a350ac311c7a2589ab7d48358ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"wT0hG2\" data-anker=\"Zdab14a350ac311c7a2589ab7d48358ad\" data-sememe-id=\"sP0tTT\">thrombocytopenia</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a>, are characteristic features of this most serious period of the disease.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>While bacterial <span data-sememe-id=\"_f15KT0\">superinfections</span> can complicate <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=U50bjg&anker=Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"U50bjg\" data-anker=\"Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-sememe-id=\"8L0Ozg\">yellow fever</a>, the progression from initial symptoms to remission followed by hemorrhagic manifestations with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a> is characteristic of viral disease progression rather than bacterial <span data-sememe-id=\"_f15KT0\">superinfection</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=U50bjg&anker=Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"U50bjg\" data-anker=\"Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-sememe-id=\"8L0Ozg\">Yellow fever</a> progresses in three periods: an initial infection period with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=YL0nwg&anker=Z67ba0252fff6842349617790ed19ae54\" data-learningcard-id=\"YL0nwg\" data-anker=\"Z67ba0252fff6842349617790ed19ae54\" data-sememe-id=\"tK0XRS\">headache</a>, followed by a remission period with symptom resolution, and finally, an intoxication period. Hemorrhagic manifestations including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hj0KbT&anker=Z5c2e48c03f4f7ffb7eba5810a71d5839\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hj0KbT\" data-anker=\"Z5c2e48c03f4f7ffb7eba5810a71d5839\" data-sememe-id=\"Vm0Geg\">epistaxis</a> and coffee-ground emesis, combined with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wT0hG2&anker=Zdab14a350ac311c7a2589ab7d48358ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"wT0hG2\" data-anker=\"Zdab14a350ac311c7a2589ab7d48358ad\" data-sememe-id=\"sP0tTT\">thrombocytopenia</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a>, are characteristic features of the intoxication period. While patients are critically ill during this period, it is not known as the critical period.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Hemorrhagic manifestations including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hj0KbT&anker=Z5c2e48c03f4f7ffb7eba5810a71d5839\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hj0KbT\" data-anker=\"Z5c2e48c03f4f7ffb7eba5810a71d5839\" data-sememe-id=\"Vm0Geg\">epistaxis</a> and coffee-ground emesis do not indicate a recurrence of the infection period but instead indicate progression to a different period of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=U50bjg&anker=Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"U50bjg\" data-anker=\"Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-sememe-id=\"8L0Ozg\">yellow fever</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=U50bjg&anker=Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"U50bjg\" data-anker=\"Z93dc20aca790221499cf385e2b0e7b8e\" data-sememe-id=\"8L0Ozg\">Yellow fever</a> progresses in three periods: an initial infection period with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=YL0nwg&anker=Z67ba0252fff6842349617790ed19ae54\" data-learningcard-id=\"YL0nwg\" data-anker=\"Z67ba0252fff6842349617790ed19ae54\" data-sememe-id=\"tK0XRS\">headache</a>, followed by a remission period with symptom resolution, and finally, an intoxication period, which occurs in approximately 15% of symptomatic patients. Hemorrhagic manifestations including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hj0KbT&anker=Z5c2e48c03f4f7ffb7eba5810a71d5839\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hj0KbT\" data-anker=\"Z5c2e48c03f4f7ffb7eba5810a71d5839\" data-sememe-id=\"Vm0Geg\">epistaxis</a> and coffee-ground emesis, combined with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wT0hG2&anker=Zdab14a350ac311c7a2589ab7d48358ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"wT0hG2\" data-anker=\"Zdab14a350ac311c7a2589ab7d48358ad\" data-sememe-id=\"sP0tTT\">thrombocytopenia</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a>, are characteristic features of the intoxication period. While this patient's symptoms have returned, this period is not known as the recrudescence period.</div>",
